a bill to ease voter registration procedures 
across the country is moving forward in the house despite 
republican warnings that it could generate fraud and complaints 
about the price tag 
lets look before we leap and were leaping here today rep 
gerald bh solomon rny said wednesday as the house moved a 
step closer to floor action on the socalled motorvoter 
legislation 
the bill calls for automatic registration of all eligible 
americans applying for drivers licenses it also would mean 
registration by post card and at various government offices 
the house in a key procedural vote on wednesday upheld by 
254166 a rule requiring critics led by gop leader bob michel of 
illinois to tie together all of their proposed amendments to the 
measure in one batch 
the rule then provides for a single vote on the entire bundle of 
proposed amendments on tuesday when the house is scheduled to take 
up the bill 
mainly republican critics chafed at the rule urging the house 
instead to junk all restrictions on how amendments may be offered 
their way would give individual amendments a better chance of 
acceptance by the house and also slow action on the bill 
