the fiscal year 
the vibrant and youthful troupe was in san diego as part of a 
west coast tour when mitchell told them the bad news 
naturally they were stunned he said in a telephone 
interview from pasadena but what was so pleasing was the 
solidarity yes we must stick together they have a vested 
interest in what we are about not just as performers but as human 
beings they put in the extra hours the extra time they do 
lectures and community outreach projects for which theyre not 
paid 
mitchell said the company has had previous layoffs but never to 
this extent weve always been very fiscally responsible our 
accumulated deficit for 20 years is about 400000 
the groups dance school in new york will remain open but the 
new york season which was scheduled to begin in may and the 
summer course will be canceled 
corporations underwrite master classes lecture demonstrations 
and other educational projects that do not generate a profit but 
the company receives little corporate support for performances 
the groups problems are shared by most in the arts community 
for the past decade many of the nations leading orchestras have 
cut back some theater groups have disappeared and a few dance 
companies have gone out of business 
in general what youre seeing is true throughout the arts a 
decline in funding due to the economy the mergers and acquisitions 
phenomenon and to a change in priority in some companies who now 
have an emphasis in the environment education and social causes at 
the expense of the arts said betsy hopkins executive director 
of the fundraising organization corporate fund for dance 
hopkins said that in general the nations 400 or so dance 
companies were healthy and not any worse off than other art forms 
theres a heightened interest in dance in this country she 
said but dance companies just dont tend to have big 
endowments 
two decades ago mitchell a talented and brash principal dancer 
from the new york city ballet sliced through the barriers that had 
kept blacks from succeeding in classical ballet and founded the 
vibrant and youthful company 
mitchell who retired from the city ballet in 1970 has led the 
troupe to international renown 
the company prides itself on preserving american dance 
repertory it also demonstrates a variety of styles and moods from 
the classical swan lake to balanchines neoclassical allegro 
brillante to the mitchells modern work holberg suite to 
the folk ballet john henry 
in 1988 the troupe captivated audiences in the soviet union 
with its magical retelling of john taras stunning firebird 
set to the original igor stravinsky score 
after engagements in berkeley calif and portland ore the 
dance theater of harlem returns to new york on feb 24 and will 
launch a major fundraising campaign in the spring 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

