a governmentsponsored dirty tricks campaign in 
northern ireland began against the irish republican army in the 
1970s but later extended to smearing top british politicians a 
former army press officer said today 
colin wallace has long maintained he was dismissed in 1975 four 
years before mrs thatcher became prime minister for threatening 
to expose the program his dismissal is now under review 
prime minister margaret thatcher on wednesday admitted she had 
wrongly denied the existence of the campaign in the past but she 
