think it does 
baker told a roomful of politicians and diplomats at the annual 
national prayer breakfast that inner security and true real 
fulfillment comes by faith it doesnt come by wielding power in a 
town where power is king 
president bush in brief remarks at the breakfast where baker 
was keynote speaker said i am convinced that the 1990s will be 
the decade of the rebirth of faith and hope the rapid 
opening of communist nations in eastern europe helped lead to that 
conviction he said 
bush also said a truly religious nation is a tolerant nation 
we cherish dissent we cherish the fact that we have many many 
faiths and we protect even the rights of disbelief 
baker said he used to think that being a success meant never 
admitting hurt or problems but that changed several years ago he 
said at that time he was having a particularly difficult problem 
and his wife susan helped him pray and see that i really needed 
to stop trying to play god and turn the matter over to faith 
baker a former treasury secretary and chief of staff under 
president reagan described his own religious feelings revealing a 
seldomseen side of a man with a smooth demeanor who usually seems 
to keep his feelings tightly controlled 
baker said he gains strength from prayer and from regular 
meetings for fellowship with a small group of very normal 
guys who just happen to hold positions of power and influence in 
washington 
the group supports one another in trying to live a life of 
faith he said 
baker characterized himself as just one person genuinely 
struggling to put faith into practice in my life 
living in a city of power and politics he said he has learned 
that power of course can be intoxicating it can be addictive 
and few doubt that power tends to corrupt and absolute power 
corrupts absolutely 
over these last nine years i have had opportunities to 
participate in the exercise of more power than i ever would have 
imagined i have felt the weight of responsibility that that brings 
and i have to admit to you as well that i have felt the temptations 
that are attendant to it baker siad 
i found early on that having a position of power really 
doesnt bring the fulfillment that many people think it does he 
said of course it does bring excitment it brings a sense of 
satisfaction when things go well disappointment when they dont 
and it brings invitations to some of the most exclusive gatherings 
in the world 
however he said for someone who likes to go to bed at 930 
at night that is not necessarily a plus 
