prison for illegal possession of swords and firearms 
but a sword and gun registration law was adopted in 1950 to 
protect culturally valuable objects which must be registered with 
the education ministry a ministry official said 21 million guns 
and swords have been registered for private ownership 
the swords must be japanese and made in traditional ways the 
guns must have been produced in japan before 1867 
