uncharacteristically personal baker gave the keynote remarks to 
the national prayer breakfast sponsored by congress he was given a 
standing ovation 
president bush also spoke briefly and vice president dan quayle 
read a new testament passage bush proclaimed his conviction that 
the 1990s will be the decade of the rebirth of faith and 
hope 
baker one of president bushs closest friends and advisers 
usually maintains a genial but reserved demeanor 
he said that during nine years in highlevel administration 
posts he has found that power does not bring fulfullment 
i found early on that having a position of power really 
doesnt bring the fulfillment that many people think it does he 
said inner security and true real fulfilment come by faith it 
doesnt come by wielding power in a town where power is king 
he told the audience of legislators and ambassadors that 
spiritual values are important in the pursuit of world peace 
the bible tells us that where the spirit of the lord is there 
is liberty so my friends i believe that as leaders we can build 
relationships around the world that are rooted in trust and love 
and understanding and i believe that we can go beyond rhetoric to 
discover concrete ways to express this reality 
baker characterized himself as just one person genuinely 
struggling to put faith into practice in my life 
he recounted an instance several years ago when i was really 
struggling with a particular problem he said he found strength 
in praying about it with his wife susan and realizing that he had 
to turn the problem over to god 
susan helped me to see that i really needed to stop trying to 
play god and turn the matter over to faith 
the 59yearold secretary also said he meets regularly for 
fellowship with a group of men he described as very normal guys 
who just happen to hold positions of power and influence in 
washington 
power of course can be intoxicating it can be addictive 
and few doubt that power tends to corrupt and absolute power 
corrupts absolutely 
over these last nine years i have had opportunities to 
participate in the exercise of more power than i ever would have 
imagined i have felt the weight of responsibility that that brings 
and i have to admit to you as well that i have felt the temptations 
that are attendant to it he said 
but power is fleeting he said noting how quickly eminent 
people lose the trappings of prestige when they lose their 
positions 
having a position of power does not bring inner security or 
fulfillment that comes only i think by developing a personal 
relationship with god which for me is personified by jesus 
christ 
baker said his journey of faith began when he started 
reading the bible 
he also talked of the importance of friendship and told how bush 
and his wife barbara had helped him through the painful period 
before and after the death of his first wife mary who died of 
cancer in 1969 
