it pay it 
the administration lobbying effort came just one day after 
president bush urged congress to keep hands off social security 
however two republican lawmakers introduced bills thursday that 
are variations of the moynihan proposal 
the two proposals 
by sen robert kasten rwis to reduce social security taxes 
in three steps to 675 percent in 1992 that would mean a 
threeyear tax cut totaling 519 for a highearning worker social 
security surpluses would no longer be considered in calculating the 
federal deficit the 1993 target date for balancing the budget 
would be extended to 1997 
by rep hank brown of colorado senior republican on the house 
ways and means subcommittee on social security to repeal this 
years tax increase take social security out of the deficit 
calculations and require the government to report annually on 
whether the pension system is sound enough to provide benefits for 
future retirees 
browns bill also would increase to 15000 a year the amount of 
wages a person between the ages of 65 and 69 may earn without 
losing any social security benefit present law takes away 1 of 
pension for each 3 of wages above 9360 
kasten said congress is almost certain to at least repeal this 
years social security tax increase he predicted lawmakers will 
reject the politics of fear which he described as allegations 
that cuts in taxes would lead to reductions in benefits 
