participate in unsponsored mediation to settle the dispute over 
the essequibo region known to have extensive mineral deposits and 
possibly oil 
perez de cuellar named alister mcintyre to head the un effort 
to end the controversy that dates back to when guyana was ruled by 
britain and venezuela by spain 
mcintyre has been vice chancellor of the university of the west 
indies in jamaica since september 1988 prior to that he was 
assistant un secretarygeneral for development and international 
economic coordination 
since the last century venezuela has claimed sovereignty over 
the essequibo region 34000 square miles located in what is now 
westcentral guyana 
the venezuelan government bases its claim of sovereignty over 
the region on colonial documents signed when venezuela was part of 
spains empire and before britain took control of territory that is 
now guyana 
in 1966 venezuelan and guyanese authorities agreed to settle the 
conflict peacefully no settlement had been reached by march 1983 
so the matter was taken to the un secretarygeneral 
