<TEXT>
one of the nations largest subsidized housing 
landlords has been suspended from future government work because of 
a fraud investigation the department of housing and urban 
development said thursday 
hud in a letter to one of the companys affiliates said the 
government has information indicating irregularities of a serious 
nature and that the company and its affiliates were being 
investigated 
the more than 40 affiliated companies are led by associated 
financial corp of california and together control nearly 50000 
units of federally assisted housing afcs president is a bruce 
rozet a prominent democratic fundraiser who in 1988 was a jesse 
jackson delegate to the democratic national convention 
rozet in a statement and additional comments issued through a 
spokesman called huds action pure harassment for political 
reasons that ultimately would harm the lowincome families the 
agency is supposed to serve 
he denied any wrongdoing and vowed to fight the suspension and 
accused hud of taking the action to avoid a hearing scheduled for 
next week on lesser sanctions against an afc affiliate 
meanwhile the washington post said in friday editions that a 
hotel partly owned by rozet wrote off a 30000 debt owed by 
jacksons 1988 presidential campaign under federal election law 
the campaign would have to report the sum either as an outstanding 
debt or as a contribution 
in this case such a contribution would be illegal because it 
comes from a corporation individual contributions are limited by 
law to 1000 per election per candidate 
jacksons campaign reports to the federal election commission 
made no mention of the bill owed to the hollywood roosevelt hotel 
in los angeles and james hewitt a lawyer for the campaign told 
the newspaper that the debt should have been listed 
the newspaper reported that the debt was written off after the 
hotel was able to collect just 45000 of an overall debt of 
75000 and cited an internal memorandum saying the unpaid balance 
was a gift from rozet 
hud general counsel francis keating said afc and its affiliates 
were being investigated by the departments inspector general law 
enforcement sources also said the us attorneys office in los 
angeles was investigating the companies 
those sources speaking on the condition of anonymity said 
charles bazarian a man rozet used as a property scout who later 
was convicted of skimming money a from hudassisted project was 
cooperating with investigators 
but the sources declined to discuss the substance of the probe 
and the los angeles prosecutor handling it lee weidman declined 
comment 
rozet and afc have had a number of runins with hud over the 
past decade including several in the last year and rozet has said 
firstyear hud secretary jack kemp has allowed bureaucrats with old 
grudges against the company to dictate hud policy toward afc 
kemp visited one afc property shortly after taking office last 
year and termed conditions there scandalous kemps top deputy 
also has called rozet and his companies slumlords 
but community leaders in several areas with afc properties have 
defended the company and rozet often is called on by congress as 
an expert on housing policy one of rozets biggest defenders in 
congress is sen alan cranston dcalif for whom rozet has been a 
major fundraiser 
hud announced the suspension in a letter to an afc affiliate 
housing resources management inc which is controlled by rozet 
partner deane e ross 
also affected by the suspension are afc and more that 40 related 
development and investment companies involved in the purchase and 
management of governmentassisted housing and the syndication of 
tax credits developers of such projects receive from the government 
afc speaking on behalf of its affiliate denied that housing 
resources management was involved in any improper activities even 
if those allegations were true afc said a suspension was 
unwarranted because the allegations involved about 35000 
afcs properties generate 80 million a year in rents the 
company said 
the suspension will have no impact on existing properties owned 
and managed by afc and its affiliates but will block the company 
indefinitely from trying to buy or manage any additional 
hudassisted properties or from seeking any new government work 
huds letter was sent to ross on friday and released by hud 
officials thursday 
in addition to the investigation hud said it had adequate 
evidence that housing resources management was involved in 
irregularities involving alleged misuse of security deposits 
and reserve funds at apartment complexes it managed in new orleans 
oklahoma and washington dc 
hud also alleged that the company was involved in requesting 
rental subsidies for vacant units and submitting false repair 
invoices at two oklahoma properties 
among the allegations hud made in the letter was that hrm 
misused security deposit accounts at southgate apartments in 
watonga okla that is the same project involved in the hudrelated 
case against bazarian 
bazarian is serving a sentence on an unrelated bank fraud 
conviction and as part of a plea agreement admitted skimming 
government funds from southgate bazarian is scheduled to be 
sentenced in that case next week 
