in the tunisian capital said the committee has been meeting since 
tuesday on the question of soviet jewish emigration 
tarassov later visited privately with plo chairman yasser arafat 
and reiterated his countrys support for an independent palestinian 
state palestinian sources said 
the soviet official also was to meet with chedli klibi 
secretary general of the arab league who said monday that soviet 
jews were being forced to emigrate to israel against their will 
neither soviet nor palestinian sources said whether tarassov 
made any commitment to control the departure of soviet jews for 
israel 
the soviet union has repeatedly expressed its opposition to 
jewish settlement in the occupied west bank and gaza strip where 
palestinian residents have waged a twoyear uprising against 
israeli rule 
israeli officials have predicted 300000 soviet jews will arrive 
in israeli in the next three years under relaxed soviet emigration 
rules 
arafat has called on the soviet union to curtail the migration 
while iraqi president saddam hussein of iraq has accused the united 
states of closing its doors to soviet jews to force the emigrants 
to settle in israel 
the united states has a global annual immigration ceiling of 
270000 
arafat and other arab leaders fear that expanded settlement of 
soviet and other jews in the territories will make a negotiated 
peace settlement with israel more difficult perhaps impossible 
presently about 70000 jews live in more that 120 settlements in 
the west bank and gaza about 12000 soviet jews arrived in israel 
last year but israeli officials expect the annual number to soar to 
more than 100000 in the next few years 
israel captured the territories in the 1967 middle east war the 
plo hopes to establish an independent state in the territories 
whose populations are overwhelmingly arab 
