<TEXT>
the government has taken control of merabank 
arizonas largest savings institution in a taxpayer bailout which 
regulators said would be softened by a 450 million cash infusion 
from the thrifts parent 
by coincidence the seizure wednesday occurred while officers of 
pinnacle west capital corp scrambled to rearrange the holding 
companys debt to accommodate extra borrowing for merabank 
agreements to restructure more than 650 million in debt with 
existing lenders were completed 15 minutes before wednesdays 
midnight deadline pinnacle west executives said 
