<TEXT>
wr grace amp co on thursday reported profits 
for the final quarter and all of 1989 rose more than 8 percent 
with the companys core specialty chemicals operations putting in a 
strong performance 
for the quarter ended dec 31 net income totaled 818 million 
or 96 cents a share up 83 percent from 755 million or 88 cents 
a share in the previous quarter revenue came to 172 billion up 
41 percent from 165 billion a year earlier 
income from continuing operations jumped 50 percent to 834 
million from 555 million a year ago 
during the quarter grace benefited from a lower tax effective 
rate partly due to a reduction in foreign taxes 
for the full year grace reported net income of 2532 million 
or 297 a share up 84 percent from 2336 million or 275 a 
share revenue amounted to 611 billion up 57 percent from 579 
billion in 1988 
income from continuing operations rose 34 percent from 1921 
million to 2566 million 
grace specialty chemicals co showed strong gains partly due to 
continued growth of the companys worldwide packaging business and 
strong results in water treatment activities and specialty 
electronics materials the company said 
grace specialty chemicals accounts for more than half of wr 
graces total sales and is the focus of its investment strategy 
specialty chemical operations received about 60 percent of 485 
million grace earmarked for capital expenditures 
the company cited significantly higher results from the pacific 
rim area which grace predicted will continue to provide 
higherthanaveraged growth rates in the future 
wr grace also reported gains in its energy specialty 
businesses and health care groups 
however the company was adversely affected in the final quarter 
and the full year by foreign currency translations 
