<TEXT>
walter loeb grew up in a european merchants 
family spent two decades working for big us department stores 
and won acclaim as the dean of retail securities analysts on wall 
street hes retiring but not really 
im calling it a graduation he saidi dont want to stop 
i want to keep going 
the new career the silverhaired bespectacled loeb is starting 
at age 65 will be as a private consultant and newsletter publisher 
in a realm in which he is considered an elder statesman 
one of the hot topics as he peers into the future is the 
prospect for global expansion by retailers shifting political 
winds traversing eastern europe and plans for greater harmony among 
european community countries in 1992 could be a stroke of good 
fortune for forwardthinking outsiders 
if retailers dont think ahead they will not have the 
opportunity because others will do it he said i think that 
unless we get ready it will not ever happen 
some prominent merchants have shown it can be done he said 
they include toys r us inc the gap inc englands laura ashley 
holdings plc and italys benetton group 
there are many examples of companies that have been able to do 
a global distribution of merchandise and i think that this will be 
the case more so in the 1990s he said 
loebs transnational vision reflects is own immigrant 
background he speaks english french german italian and spanish 
i think its a very exciting new topic he said in an 
interview as he was preparing to leave morgan stanley amp co launch 
loeb associates and start a a monthly newsletter 
stores supplying staples that transcend cultural differences 
should have the easiest time venturing from home turf the giant 
toy discounter toys r us is one of the best examples toys are 
toys kids are kids and grandparents are grandparents loeb said 
with retailers worldwide looking toward european expansion he 
said the value of american properties currently for sale has 
fallen because the siren song of foreign markets has diverted 
investor attention 
for instance loeb said the debtencumbered allied stores corp 
and federated department stores inc chains owned by canadas 
campeau corp which are trying to solve their financial problems 
in bankruptcy court may not fetch as much as they might have if 
they were auctioned 
loeb said many widely publicized predicaments in retailing were 
caused by brash developers with no merchandising expertise the 
financial drain of building retail operations largely with 
borrowed money overshadowed the core business of selling goods 
im sad about developments that have been caused by 
developers i believe very strongly that merchants should be 
running the retail businesses loeb said its not a science 
but it is also not easy to be a good merchant 
after the shakeout more stores will be back in the hands of 
retailers loeb predicted 
tomorrow some of these companies will again be smaller 
entities he said entrepreneurs will run them maybe with 
high debt but they will be run on an entrepreneurial basis and 
several will be very successful as a result 
even exemplary retailers will have to adapt in the 1990s as 
consumers save more spend less and redirect dollars toward 
housewares and home improvement i think the consumer is going to 
be very conservative loeb said 
stores appealing to doityourselfers stand to flourish while 
specialty apparel retailers which had been gobbling up market 
share from traditional department stores will have a tougher 
time he said 
personally loeb said he frequents discounters because like any 
savvy consumer he likes a good bargain but he patronizes 
specialty apparel stores when shopping for suits 
i like the service i like the attention and i like the 
quality of the tailoring he said 
friends and acquaintances describe loeb as loyal and 
selfeffacing with a ready sense of humor he takes obvious pride 
in the accomplishments of his three adult daughters and of his wife 
of 31 years phyllis 
professional contacts admire his keen judgment and ferocious 
appetite for work 
underneath an affable exterior he is germanic in work 
habits said isaac lagnado director of research at the 
international council of shopping centers 
loeb was born jan 28 1925 near frankfurt his father karl a 
successful button wholesaler moved his family and business to 
italy in 1936 when nazi germany was in the throes of antisemitic 
political upheaval 
the loebs left italy in 1939 for america they relocated in cuba 
for 18 months while awaiting entry into this country where the 
elder loeb established himself as a wholesaler of costume jewelry 
walter loeb was drafted into the army in 1943 and participated 
in the normandy invasion he was at utah beach on dday 
upon his return to the united states he studied marketing and 
history at new york university and graduated in 1949 
he spent 20 years learning the retail business from the inside 
he worked at an arm of what is now rh macy amp co at may 
department stores co and at allied stores corp 
loeb turned to consulting in 1969 then came to wall street in 
1972 as an analyst with the johnson redbook service he joined 
morgan stanley in 1974 as a senior analystwas named a vice 
president in 1980 and a principal of the firm in 1984 
dubbed the dean of wall street retail analysts by industry 
insiders loeb also has won recognition internationally the french 
newspaper le monde in a 1988 article on a speech loeb made in 
paris referred to him somewhat irreverently as the pope of 
business 
experience in retailing has helped loeb cultivate a rapport with 
store executives that few in his field enjoy it also endowed him 
with special influence among institutional investors he has advised 
i did everything that one does as you grow up in this 
business he said 
</TEXT>
