grumman corp on thursday reported a sharp drop 
in earnings for the 1989 fourth quarter and year in part because 
of lower sales in its aerospace and electronics sectors 
in a statement the company said it planned to reduce its work 
force by about 1000 by the end of 1990 following 3000 cuts in 
1989 that left the defense contractor with 28900 employees 
an imminent decline in defense spending by the federal 
government because of easing eastwest tensions has been blamed for 
a poor outlook for the defense industry 
for the period ended dec 31 grumman said profits dropped 39 
percent to 148 million or 41 cents a share from 241 million 
or 70 cents a share in the same 1988 period 
sales for the quarter fell 16 percent to 867 million from 104 
million 
for the full year net income was 673 million or 191 a 
share down 22 percent from 865 million or 250 a share in 
1988 sales declined 25 percent to 356 billion from 365 
billion 
grumman said sales from its aerospace division fell 58 percent 
because of winding down of two development programs and delivery of 
fewer production aircraft to the navy 
grummans electronics sales declined 133 percent because of 
fewer test equipment deliveries reduced requirements for grumman 
aircraft and lower revenue from an air force and army joint radar 
program 
even in a nogrowth defense budget cycle there will be plenty 
of business for grumman and others who are efficient reliable 
suppliers of quality products grumman chairman john obrien said 
in a statement 
