<TEXT>
gannett co inc reported thursday its profit rose 81 percent 
in the fourth quarter while another media giant knightridder 
inc posted a 312 percent increase in earnings from continuing 
operations for the same period 
meanwhile mcgrawhill inc reported a loss of 983 million for 
the quarter as a result of previously disclosed plans to take 
unusual charges 
gannett said its earnings increased despite a weakening economy 
partly because of the diversity of its holdings 
the arlington vabased company which publishes usa today and 
81 other daily newspapers said it earned 1274 million or 79 
cents a share in the three months ended dec 31 compared with 
1178 million or 73 cents a share a year earlier 
fourthquarter revenue rose 7 percent to 9686 million from 
9053 million a year earlier 
for the year gannett earned 3975 million or 247 a share 
up 93 percent from 3645 million or 226 a share a year 
earlier 
operating revenue rose 6 percent to 352 billion from 331 
billion a year earlier 
