201 a share in contrast to earnings of 55 million or 113 a 
share a year earlier 
the latest loss reflects a charge of 152 million after taxes 
reflecting a realignment of operations writedowns associated with 
its data resources and other units the shutdown of its general 
books unit and reserves for severance payments associated with 
staff reductions of more than 1000 positions 
the company said in december that it planned to make those 
charges against its fourthquarter earnings 
