the brokerage industry its school publishing venture with 
macmillan had an operating loss for the quarter which is 
seasonally weak 
joseph l dionne chairman and chief executive of mcgrawhill 
said he expects the company to earn 350 to 4 a share excluding 
nonrecurring gains in 1990 
