<TEXT>
standard amp poors corp said thursday it 
downgraded its rating on 400 million of texas air corp senior 
debt because of heavy losses at texas airs subsidiary eastern 
airlines and a new reorganization plan proposed by eastern 
the credit rating agency said the 400 million in texas air 
senior debt remained on its surveillance list with negative 
implications 
art kent a spokesman for texas air at its headquarters in 
houston said the company had no immediate comment on standard amp 
poors action 
on tuesday a committee of easterns preferred shareholders 
suggested the liquidation or outright sale of the miamibased 
airline which has been in chapter 11 bankruptcy reorganization 
since last march 
in papers filed in us bankruptcy court the committee said it 
had lost faith in easterns management because it was 
cannibalizing the airline by selling vital assets 
the preferred shareholders criticized easterns latest 
reorganization plan unveiled late last week which proposes to pay 
them no more than 10 cents on the dollar in the form of new stock 
the new plan also calls for paying unsecured creditors only 10 
percent of their debts in cash when the airline emerges from 
bankruptcy protection and another 70 percent over the following 10 
years without interest 
in return for accepting partial repayment texas air would give 
the unsecured creditors 40 percent of easterns equity 
under easterns two previous plans unsecured creditors 
primarily trade suppliers such as aircraft manufacturers were to 
be repaid in full with interest at the completion of chapter 11 
easterns heavy losses and revised reorganization proposal 
which foresees a reduced cash payout to unsecured creditors will 
result in additional demands on texas airs resources and severely 
constrain financial flexibility standard amp poors said in a 
statement 
the parent company is already paying interest and dividends on 
some eastern secured debt and preferred stock and funded part of 
easterns september pension payment 
the rating agency stressed that texas airs cash reserves should 
prevent any liquidity crisis and that continental airlines its 
other major subsidiary is recovering from earlier financial 
problems 
however standard amp poors said credit strength is damaged by 
easterns continuing difficulties 
the statement also referred to reported remarks tuesday by texas 
air chairman frank lorenzo that a merger of eastern and continental 
is a possibility 
while a combination has longterm potential it would risk 
reversing the substantial progress made at continental the 
agency said 
texas air in a statement issued late thursday said it has 
studied the merger option but no consolidation of eastern and 
continental is currently being planned or being proposed by texas 
air to easterns creditors 
in a related development wednesday us bankruptcy judge burton 
r lifland approved easterns request for 50 million to be taken 
out of escrow to help fund its operations through february 
also on wednesday easterns management issued a memo to its 
employees dismissing the preferred shareholders criticisms and 
persistent rumors of a possible chapter 7 liquidation 
