the securities and exchange commission is 
conducting an inquiry into a 400 million charge that first 
interstate bancorp reported dec 7 for loan losses mostly at its 
texas subsidiary the bank has disclosed 
first interstate said sec staffers made an informal inquiry 
last month requesting and receiving documents from the bank 
