<TEXT>
smithkline beecham thursday cut the price of 
its popular high blood pressure drug dyazide by 11 percent one day 
after its sole generic competitor removed its version of the drug 
from the market 
the pharmaceutical giant said the move was in response to a 
request by us rep john dingell dmich chairman of the house 
energy and commerce investigations subcommittee who feared some 
patients wouldnt be able to afford the brandname drug 
smithklines move effective saturday will lower the price from 
about 36 cents a capsule to an estimated 32 cents company 
spokesman jeremy heymsfeld said 
bolar pharmaceutical co incs generic version had cost about 
25 cents a capsule he said a typical patient takes one capsule a 
day 
bolar recalled their capsules wednesday following disclosures 
that the company allegedly gave false test data to the food and 
drug administration for its version of dyazide 
it is a welcome gesture in the direction of price equity 
dingell said in a statement responding to the price cut dingell 
had said wednesday that if smithkline did not cut the price the 
fda should consider requiring smithkline to reformulate the drug so 
it would be easier to copy 
frederick kyle president of smithkline beecham 
pharaceuticalus said the decision to cut the price took into 
consideration the needs of stockholders employees and patients 
we recognize that for some patients the unavailability of a 
generic version will represent an increase in their health care 
expenditures to help minimize the impact we are decreasing the 
price of dyazide kyle said 
in 1988 the first full year of generic competition for dyazide 
sales in this country were 153 million a 52 percent drop from 
1987 
the fda said patients taking bolars generic drug should 
continue taking the drug until their prescription runs out and 
arrange with their physicians to take another medication 
last spring vitarine pharmaceuticals of springfield gardens 
ny took its version of dyazide off the market after it admitted 
cheating on fda tests 
</TEXT>
