mccaw cellular communications inc the 
nations largest cellular telephone company said it reduced its 
losses in the fourth quarter of 1989 and boosted revenues by 67 
percent 
mccaw also announced thursday it has completed negotiations with 
its agent banks on a credit agreement to finance its tender offer 
for 219 million shares of lin broadcasting of new york 
the 338 billion deal will give mccaw control of lin a major 
step in the companys drive to serve the nations largest 
population centers 
mccaw also said it expects to close in february the pending sale 
of its southcentral cellular systems to contel cellular inc for 
approximately 13 billion 
for the quarter ended dec 31 mccaw lost 584 million or 36 
cents a share on revenues of 1522 million compared with a loss 
of 922 million or 70 cents a share on revenues of 913 million a 
year earlier 
for the year mccaw lost 2885 million or 195 a share on 
revenues of 5041 million compared with a loss of 297 million or 
239 a share on revenues of 3108 million in 1988 
our growth in revenues cash flow and subscribers continues to 
meet or exceed our expectations said craig mccaw chairman and 
chief executive officer 
cash flow representing income from operations before 
depreciation and amortization rose to 191 million in the latest 
quarter from 500000 a year earlier 
mccaw cellular has been developing major regional systems that 
are important to the creation of a national cellular network the 
deals with lin and contel will give mccaw and lin a strong 
concentration in california texas florida new york and 
pennsylvania mccaw said 
mccaw credited the improved fourthquarter performance to 
reduced losses from operations gains on sales of securities and 
some cellular interests and a significant rise in interest income 
from the money received from british telecoms purchase of a 20 
percent interest in mccaw cellular 
the number of cellular subscribers in its markets as well as 
markets where it has the right to buy a controlling interest rose 
68 percent to 434000 at yearnd from 258000 at the end of 1988 
