<TEXT>
don simpson and jerry bruckheimer the 
producers of top gun and beverly hills cop signed an 
exclusive fiveyear deal with paramount pictures to make at least 
five films the studio announced 
the terms of the partnership were not disclosed but the 
arrangement is likely to make simpson and bruckheimer the most 
successful movie producers in hollywood in the 80s also the most 
highly compensated 
furthermore the pair will enjoy the independence to make any 
movie any way they want 
they paramount put up the money we put up the talent we 
meet at the theater simpson said wednesday 
in recent years the producing duo have made some of the 
biggestgrossing films in movie history 
their boxoffice hits include 1983s flashdance 209 
million worldwide boxoffice gross 1984s beverly hills cop 
312 million 1986s top gun 351 million and 1987s 
beverly hills cop ii 281 million 
their only flop was 1984s thief of hearts the two have 
produced films for paramount for the last seven years 
the deal was struck after months of negotiations with paramount 
and other studios simpson and bruckheimer said they also 
considered taking their production company public but declined to 
do so because they wanted to be handson producers 
we ended up with what we were after from the beginning 
freedom simpson said said bruckheimer we have the right to 
make a certain number of pictures under certain limits but very 
broad limits 
unlike most producers under contract to a studio simpson and 
bruckheimer will develop and make motion pictures without the 
advice and consent of paramount executives 
paramount will provide financing in the range of 20 million per 
film and then market and distribute the finished products 
were not compelled to do anything simpson said were 
not serving managements needs we dont have any bosses 
paramount will continue to negotiate contracts for the 
producers and simpson and bruckheimer do not expect to have to 
hire additional personnel 
while neither paramount nor simpson and bruckheimer revealed the 
terms of the deal it is almost certain that the pair will collect 
a substantial share of their films profits on top of that they 
will earn a producers fee for the films they make to make big 
money though they have to make popular movies 
the two also will be allowed to direct movies and plan to 
codirect their next project 
directing bruckheimer said is another horizon to tackle 
its always been important to conquer new goals and its more 
control over the creative process 
the pair said they have no aspirations to run a studio as 
producers jon peters and peter guber did last year when they exited 
warner bros to assume management of columbia pictures 
the simpsonbruckheimer production company located on the 
paramount lot is now filming the auto racing movie days of 
thunder starring tom cruise robert duvall nicole kidman and 
randy quaid simpson himself will play an italian racecar driver 
in the movie it is directed by top guns tony scott 
before joining with bruckheimer to produce flashdance 
simpson was paramounts president of worldwide production for two 
years bruckheimer as an independent producer has worked on 
american gigolo the remake of cat people and thief 
